North-RhineWestphalia is raising 1.2 billion marks through a 10-yeardomestic bond with a coupon of 6-1/8 pct and priced at 100.20,lead manager Westdeutsche Landesbank Girozentrale, WestLB,said.    The bonds yield 6.10 pct at issue, and will be sold fromApril 2 to 7. Payment date is April 17, and the bond matures onthe same date in 1997. Some one billion marks will be issuedfor immediate sale, and the remaining 200 mln marks will be setaside for market regulation.    Listing will be on all eight West German exchanges. REUTER&#3;